abstract: In their own words, here is how the House managers and President Trump’s defense team view impeachment.
snippet: In their own words, here is how the House managers and President Trump’s defense team view impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A former police chief, a prosecutor who won the conviction of an F.B.I. agent and one of Texas’ first Latina representatives. A constitutional law professor who once defended O.J. Simpson against a murder charge, a former special prosecutor who pursued the impeachment of President Bill Clinton and a litigator for the Christian right.

abstract: President Trump arrived Tuesday to hold a rally in the state — his first there since taking office — where registered Democrats outnumber Republicans by a million voters.
snippet: President Trump arrived Tuesday to hold a rally in the state — his first there since taking office — where registered Democrats outnumber Republicans by a million voters.
lead_paragraph: WILDWOOD, N.J. — The crowds in this oceanfront town swelled well beyond their usual winter size on Tuesday, filled with thousands of President Trump’s supporters who had braved bitter cold, lack of sleep and long lines for a chance to hear him speak.

abstract: With or without witnesses, Trump’s trial shows that the antifederalists were right to question the Senate’s purpose.
snippet: With or without witnesses, Trump’s trial shows that the antifederalists were right to question the Senate’s purpose.
lead_paragraph: Last week, after Senate Republicans voted unanimously to approve their leader Mitch McConnell’s rules for President Trump’s impeachment trial — fast-tracking the process and putting up barriers to the production of evidence and witnesses, Representative Jerry Nadler of New York, one of seven impeachment managers, despaired over the strong chance that voters would not get a fair, comprehensive hearing of the case against the president.

abstract: Their rhetorical choices have grave implications for the meaning of the acquittal the president is likely to receive.

lead_paragraph: The Constitution says that what’s happening in the Senate right now is a trial. But it’s no ordinary trial: As we’re all now well aware, a Senate trial is a hybrid affair, part law and part politics.

headline_main: Why Trump’s Lawyers Should Talk Like Lawyers

abstract: President Trump’s legal team will complete oral arguments as negotiations accelerate over whether to include witnesses in the trial.
snippet: President Trump’s legal team will complete oral arguments as negotiations accelerate over whether to include witnesses in the trial.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers will complete their third and final day of oral arguments on Tuesday, wrapping up a defense that has sought to give Republican senators reasonable doubt and present them with alternative explanations for the president’s actions toward Ukraine.

headline_main: What to Watch For in Trump’s Impeachment Trial on Tuesday

abstract: With Republicans now unified, it is difficult to find a district where a challenger can credibly claim that the incumbent has been insufficiently supportive of the president.
snippet: With Republicans now unified, it is difficult to find a district where a challenger can credibly claim that the incumbent has been insufficiently supportive of the president.
lead_paragraph: DOYLESTOWN, Pa. — The scene was almost quaint, this cowboy-hatted neophyte preaching his gospel as about 15 supporters, peering out from snow-drenched hoodies, nodded along. Glimpsed from afar, it seemed a reminder that even in 2020, politics still boils down to this: small-town voters braving the elements to listen to an underdog candidate speak truth to power.

abstract: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
snippet: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden has no trouble lingering in place, wherever he is, especially if there’s a point he wants to finish — or start. Generally it does not matter how many people are prodding him along or waiting out in the cold. And it seemed important to Biden that I hear what he was talking about right now before we finished.

abstract: Three new books cover the different ways and reasons that we’ve ended up divided.
snippet: Three new books cover the different ways and reasons that we’ve ended up divided.
lead_paragraph: This month has brought a surfeit of interesting new books about American politics, most of them attempts to explain exactly how we reached our current era of gridlock and demagogy, in which disliked establishments and disreputable populists clash by night.

abstract: The Kremlin is increasing arms sales, security pacts and training programs as the American defense secretary weighs withdrawing troops from the continent.
snippet: The Kremlin is increasing arms sales, security pacts and training programs as the American defense secretary weighs withdrawing troops from the continent.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nearly 200 Russian mercenaries have deployed in recent months to Mozambique to combat a growing Islamic State offshoot there, even as Moscow is taking initial steps toward building a military port in the Horn of Africa that could become Russia’s first permanent base on the continent.
